[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpqynhputw[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing run against Apache Tika’s untarring functionality triggered a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical file path traversal finding. The fuzzer drove [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar` via a harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuilt-in FilePathTraversal sanitizer in Jazzer flagged an input that attempts to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite outside the intended extraction directory.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue observed  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During a libFuzzer-powered Jazzer session, the call chain reached [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.main`, which extracts entries from a TAR archive. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJazzer’s FilePathTraversal sanitizer detected an output path that escapes the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintended extraction root [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. writing to `…[0m[35m/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and raised a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical`.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  File path traversal during archive extraction. The sanitizer reports that an [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive entry’s path allows writing files outside the target directory.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The crash log shows the sanitizer hook [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`FilePathTraversal.checkPath`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintercepting a path argument in `TikaUntar.main`.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Multiple Apache Commons Compress and IO classes [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `TarArchiveInputStream`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`IOUtils`, `FileUtils`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m were instrumented, indicating the code under test heavily [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muses those libraries for unpacking.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m simply invokes Tika’s CLI untar logic; [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit is not responsible for path sanitization but exposes the vulnerable code to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for investigation  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar` – review how it builds target file paths from [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive entry names and whether it normalizes or restricts them.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Underlying archive-processing classes from Apache Commons Compress [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TarArchiveInputStream`, `ArchiveEntry`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to see how entry names are read and passed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malong.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Any utility methods in Tika or surrounding code that handle path joining or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory creation for extracted entries.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to confirm that it does[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot alter extraction behavior and faithfully mirrors the CLI logic.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• A libFuzzer/Jazzer run against the TikaTar unpacking CLI [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaUntar.main`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreported a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path traversal` for the path [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/tmp/.../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The crash log shows that the sanitizer hook in [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.FilePathTraversal` was invoked when [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing an entry named `jazzer-traversal`, triggered from `TikaUntar.main` and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpropagated through the fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• This demonstrates that entries with relative paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`..[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the TAR archive can[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mescape the extraction directory, posing a clear directory traversal vulnerability.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• In `TikaUntar.java`, before iterating entries, a new variable [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`normalizedExtractDir` is defined as `[0m[1;35mextractDir.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Inside the loop, the patch replaces the previous target resolution with  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      Path target = [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mnormalizedExtractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  and adds a guard  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnormalizedExtractDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid entry outside extraction directory: "[0m[39m + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The patch ensures that any resolved entry path is checked against the normalized [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction root and rejects entries that escape it.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult After Patch  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• A subsequent fuzzer run logs instrumentation messages as before and then surfaces[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma `java.io.IOException: Invalid entry outside extraction directory: [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m..[0m[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• This IOException is wrapped in a `RuntimeException` in the harness [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, leading to the same non-zero exit code [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m77[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The presence of the new exception message confirms that the path normalization [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand boundary check are invoked when handling malicious entries.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Verify handling of directory entries [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mtae.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, symbolic links, and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhard links in TAR archives—those might similarly enable escapes.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Inspect other archive-handling code paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., ZIP unpacking in Tika[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistent normalization and boundary checks.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Examine how `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` invokes `TikaUntar.main` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe harness[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure exceptions are reported appropriately but not misclassified as crashes [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munrelated to security checks.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Review canonicalization vs. normalization semantics in Java’s `Path` API, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mespecially on Windows or when mount points are involved.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Audit additional file-system operations in the codebase [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., file writes in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother CLI commands[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for analogous traversal risks.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer log shows a critical file path traversal finding in `TikaUntar.main`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mraised by `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.FilePathTraversal.check` when [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe code attempted to extract a tar entry with a path escaping the intended [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `[0m[35m/tmp/expander-.../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The exception stack traces through `TikaUntar.main` and into the fuzzer harness [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, terminating with exit status [0m[1;36m77[0m[39m and producing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma Java reproducer.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No normalization or path checks existed in the original `TikaUntar` code; entries[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere written directly via `[0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizers loaded by Jazzer flagged the out-of-bounds path before any [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplication logic caught it.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The harness code [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m simply invokes `TikaUntar.main` and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpropagates any exceptions as crashes.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `TikaUntar.main`, the patch introduces:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `normalizedExtractDir = [0m[1;35mextractDir.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. For each `TarArchiveEntry tae`:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Resolve the target path:  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `Path target = [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mnormalizedExtractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - If `![0m[1;35mtarget.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnormalizedExtractDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, throw `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mentry outside extraction directory: "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - If `[0m[1;35mtae.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, call `[0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtarget[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Else if `[0m[1;35mtae.isSymbolicLink[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mtae.isLink[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, throw `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mlink entry in archive: "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Else [0m[1;39m([0m[39mregular file[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ensure parent directories exist and write file [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontents.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Directory and file handling code was reorganized under these checks.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer log still crashes but at a different point: it now throws  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  `java.lang.RuntimeException: something went very, very wrong`  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  caused by the custom `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid entry outside extraction directory: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m../../jazzer-traversal"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m47[0m[39m of `TikaUntar.java`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This indicates the new path-escaping entry is caught by the manual check, and an [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception is thrown instead of proceeding.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The harness wraps that `IOException` inside a `RuntimeException`, still [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsidered a crash by libFuzzer, leading to exit status [0m[1;36m77[0m[39m.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFurther Investigation  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Review `TikaUntar.main`’s exception handling strategy to determine whether [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrowing an `IOException` is the desired outcome for malicious or malformed [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchives, or if it should skip such entries silently.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Examine how `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne` and `fuzzerTestOneInput` propagate [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceptions—consider catching `IOException` arising from invalid entries to avoid [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer crashes that are not genuine application failures.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Audit other archive-related code paths in `tika-cli` and in upstream Tika archive[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mutilities to ensure consistent path normalization and traversal protection across [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer-based libFuzzer run against `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` uncovered a security [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer exception: a file path traversal when unpacking a TAR archive in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaUntar.main`. To mitigate this, a patch was proposed that iterates through each[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TarArchiveEntry`, resolves and normalizes the extraction path, and skips entries [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat lie outside the intended directory or represent links. After applying the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch, the Maven build failed with two compilation errors indicating that the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msymbol `normalizedExtractDir` could not be found in `TikaUntar.java`.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During fuzzing, Jazzer reported a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path [0m        [2m                [0m
